.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1S "11 August 2025" "VERSION" "MANUAL_NAME"

.SH NAME
shell \- brief description of what the program does

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple shell
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.RI [ ARGUMENTS ]
.br
.B simple_shell
.RB { \-h | \-\-help }
.br
.B simple_shell
.RB { \-V | \-\-version }

.SH DESCRIPTION
Detailed description of what the program does, its purpose, and general behavior.
This section should provide a comprehensive overview that helps users understand
when and why they would use this program.

You can continue with multiple paragraphs here. Each paragraph should be
separated by a blank line in the source.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit.

.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit.

.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output mode.

.TP
.BI \-f " FILE" ", \-\-file=" FILE
Specify input file. Replace FILE with the actual file path.

.TP
.BI \-o " OUTPUT" ", \-\-output=" OUTPUT
Specify output directory or file.

.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-recursive
Process directories recursively.

.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Show what would be done without actually doing it.

.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I FILE
Input file to process. Can be specified multiple times.

.TP
.I DIRECTORY
Target directory for operations.

.SH EXIT STATUS
The program exits with one of the following values:
.TP
.B 0
Successful completion.

.TP
.B 1
General error occurred.

.TP
.B 2
Invalid command line arguments.

.TP
.B 126
Command found but not executable.

.TP
.B 127
Command not found.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Basic usage:
.B program_name file.txt

.TP
Process multiple files with verbose output:
.B program_name \-v file1.txt file2.txt file3.txt

.TP
Use specific output directory:
.B program_name \-o /tmp/output input_file.txt

.TP
Recursive processing with dry-run:
.B program_name \-r \-\-dry\-run /path/to/directory

.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/program_name/config
User configuration file.

.TP
.I /etc/program_name.conf
System-wide configuration file.

.TP
.I /var/log/program_name.log
Default log file location.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PROGRAM_NAME_CONFIG
Override default configuration file path.

.TP
.B PROGRAM_NAME_DEBUG
Enable debug mode when set to any non-empty value.

.TP
.B HOME
Used to locate user configuration files.

.SH DIAGNOSTICS
Common error messages and their meanings:

.TP
.B "Permission denied"
The program lacks necessary permissions to access a file or directory.

.TP
.B "File not found"
Specified input file does not exist.

.TP
.B "Invalid option"
An unrecognized command line option was provided.

